question_text: What is the difference between a test print and an OS test page?
answer_options: A test print comes from an application, OS test page is from printer memory
A test print is printed by the OS, while OS test page is sent by firmware
An OS test page is initiated through the OS, while test print can originate from the printer interface
correct_answer: An OS test page is initiated through the OS, while test print can originate from the printer interface
explanation: An OS test page is generated by the operating system, while a printer self-test or test print originates from the printerâ€™s onboard menu.
